%I A393810 #39 Apr 11 2026 17:46:12
%S A393810 1,9,270,8154,259209,8529921,287329140,9841383288,341309814858,
%T A393810 11951985351834,421773730944084,14977884769617708,534677344017297858,
%U A393810 19171218712802918706,689996917303356051792,24915114884708594195832,902230812743891520644937,32753980020160125318149649
%N A393810 Expansion of 2F1(1/6, 1/2; 1/2; 27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2.
%C A393810 Integer sequence arising from the symmetric square of a Gauss hypergeometric function composed with a degree-3 Belyi map phi(x) = 27*x/(1-4*x)^3. Not an Apery-like sequence: no order-2 polynomial recurrence was found up to degree 12.
%H A393810 Alex Shvets, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19387246">Integer sequences from Sym^2(2F1) Belyi pullback scan</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%F A393810 a(n) = [x^n] 2F1(1/6, 1/2; 1/2; 27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2.
%F A393810 Recurrence: (3*n+4)*(n+3)*a(n+3) - 3*(39*n^2+143*n+124)*a(n+2) + 144*(n+1)*(n+2)*a(n+1) - 64*n*(3*n+7)*a(n) = 0.
%F A393810 a(n) ~ cosh(arcsinh(1)/3)^(1/3) * (1 + 2*cosh(arccosh(3)/3))^(3*n) / (2^(1/6) * Gamma(1/3) * n^(2/3)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 30 2026
%e A393810 For n=0 the recurrence gives (3*0+4)*(0+3)*a(3) - 3*(39*0^2+143*0+124)*a(2) + 144*(0+1)*(0+2)*a(1) - 64*0*(3*0+7)*a(0) = 0, i.e., 12*a(3) - 372*270 + 288*9 = 0, so a(3) = 8154.
%t A393810 CoefficientList[Series[Hypergeometric2F1[1/6, 1/2,1/2, 27x/(1-4x)^3]^2,{x,0,17}],x] (* _Stefano Spezia_, Mar 29 2026 *)
